{{- define "format-messages" -}}
{{- range $i, $m := .Messages -}}
{{- if $i}}

{{end -}}
{{- if $m.IsVoice -}}
Decoded user's speech to text (may be inaccurate): {{$m.Text}}
{{- else -}}
{{- $m.Text -}}
{{- end -}}
{{- end -}}
{{- if .Files}}

Attached files:
{{- range .Files}}
  {{.Path}} ({{.Type}}, {{.Size}})
{{- end -}}
{{- end -}}
{{- end}}


{{- define "reply-instructions" -}}
{{- $reply := "send_message" -}}
{{- $progress := "send_progress" -}}
{{- if .IsVoice -}}
{{- $reply = "send_verbal_reply" -}}
{{- $progress = "send_verbal_progress" -}}
User can only hear you now; keep it conversational, no markdown.
IMPORTANT: Never put more than one question in a single message. Wait for the answer before asking the next question.

{{end -}}
The TUI is invisible to the user. EVERY user-visible message — questions, status, final answers, errors — must go through `{{$reply}}` or `{{$progress}}`. Plain text in your response is never seen by the user.

- If the request is ambiguous, risky, or destructive, confirm with `{{$reply}}` BEFORE acting. Otherwise just proceed.
- Use `{{$progress}}` for non-blocking status updates during long work.
- When the task is done, deliver the result with `{{$reply}}` and wait. NEVER end your turn without calling `{{$reply}}` — going silent looks like a crash to the user.
- For long-running multi-step work, call `check_messages` between steps to stay responsive.
{{- end}}
